it's okay with you?

99
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:23,267
You understood that when you
met Sahoko, don't you?

100
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:26,867
Why would I complain
when I get to marry a girl like her?

101
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:33,400
You're right.

102
00:07:42,133 --> 00:07:43,500
Naoki is

103
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:47,100
really marrying that girl.

104
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:51,267
We can't go back anymore.

105
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:07,200
<i>Miss Kotoko Aihara.</i>

106
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:11,133
Will you marry me?

107
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:15,400
Marrying Kin-chan, huh?

108
00:08:20,367 --> 00:08:23,000
I can't picture myself.

109
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,733
-Yes.
-Kotoko, may I come in?

110
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,033
Yes.

111
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,633
What is it, Dad?

112
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:37,567
Kotoko.

113
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:40,167
Can you take a look at this?

114
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:48,333
-Is this the new house?
-Yeah.

115
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:50,000
How do you like it?

116
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:51,833
It's bigger than before.

117
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:55,533
It's a little far from the station,
but the rent is reasonable.

118
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:58,967
Didn't you tell me that you
didn't like this kind?

119
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:01,433
You said you liked
a single-family home.

120
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:06,267
Owning a single-family home was
a promise that I made with your mom.

121
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:09,133
But it's impossible to get one
right now.

122
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,833
So we'll go with a rental for now.

123
00:09:12,767 --> 00:09:15,800
If you marry a man,
I'll aim for owning

124
00:09:15,967 --> 00:09:19,367
a two generation home with him.

125
00:09:20,067 --> 00:09:22,433
Of course, if there's a guy

126
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,367
who wants to marry you.

127
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:37,633
Dad.

128
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:43,367
Will you be happy
if I marry Kin-chan?

129
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:49,400
Is anything going on
between you and him?

130
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:52,167
-I'm just asking.
-Oh.

131
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,333
Kinnosuke, huh?

132
00:09:57,733 --> 00:09:59,033
Well, he sure is

133
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,600
talented when it comes to cooking.

134
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:06,233
He's warmhearted and caring.

135
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:09,433
So honest and sincere.

136
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,667
If he marries you,

137
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,767
I'll have a successor
for my restaurant.

138
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:16,367
I'll be happy about it.

139
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:22,167
I agree.

140
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:26,600
But you don't have to force yourself
to marry him.

141
00:10:26,767 --> 00:10:29,900
Your feelings are the most important
thing to me.

142
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:32,633
If you love this man the most

143
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,300
and he'll make you happy,

144
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:38,867
then the restaurant
has nothing to do with it.

145
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:53,433
Don't turn around yet.

146
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,033
-After you get up there.
-Okay.

147
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,233
Not yet.

148
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:57,833
-Not yet.
-Yes.

149
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,833
Here we come.
Here we come.

150
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:03,033
One, two, three, ta-da!

151
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,100
Amazing.

152
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,267
Kotoko, look.

153
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:11,367
It's so beautiful.

154
00:11:11,833 --> 00:11:14,500
How about that, Kotoko?
Let's go.

155
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,133
I know the best seat.

156
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,167
The special seat for you.

157
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,133
There, there.

158
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:24,200
There, there. This way, this way.

159
00:11:24,567 --> 00:11:26,133
See?

160
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:28,000
How about this?

161
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:30,400
Take a look.

162
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,600
How do you like it?

163
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:35,633
It's huge.

164
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:38,433
It's so cool.

165
00:11:38,733 --> 00:11:41,067
It's impossible to block this.

166
00:11:41,233 --> 00:11:43,233
<i>I'm</i>

167
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,600
telling you that I don't mind

168
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:48,067
being in the same house with you.

169
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:50,100
Does that mean that

170
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,700
you don't

171
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:57,167
hate me?

172
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:59,667
You're hard to deal with,

173
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,700
but I don't hate you.

174
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:06,633
Kotoko.

175
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:12,233
Rainbow Bridge is over there.

176
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:15,267
Hey, Kotoko.

177
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,233
Kotoko.

178
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:21,200
Sorry, nothing.

179
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,333
I know. You must be hungry.

180
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:29,033
Shall we go eat something
before we go play?

181
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:31,200
When you're hungry,

182
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:35,600
